caption: The Silver Factory was a lovely gem to discover here in our neighborhood ! I’ve ordered takeout from here before but it was lovely to actually go and check it out.  This restaurant/ bar has a instagramable element to the environment. It’s the perfect little spot to grab a bite with friends or go on a date. The staff was attentive and the food was filling and very good !  We got the pomegranate and peach soju ( which was great to share among a group of four ).  The chicken wings with soy garlic sauce was a MUST. They’re shareable dishes we’re all great.  I would stop by this place and check it out. I will be revisiting soon!
Great hangout spot with fantastic food!

The food was amazing! Very nice atmosphere. Also tried a new dish which will be added to the menu very soon and it was soooooo good. Photo attached. Looks simple, but it is highly recommended. Unfortunately it’s the only picture we got today.

Delivery was late.  Food was lukewarm at best, and chicken wings soggy and not worth eating as a result.  The glass noodle stir fry with vegetables was just a massive pile of noodles with very few vegetables (2 pieces of broccoli and some greens on top, but the rest was just a pile of carbs, unlike photo when ordering).  The Bulgogi was good, but am sure it was much better before having to be microwaved.

Did not taste authentic at all. There were potatoes in my soondubu jjigae, which I have never heard and didn’t enjoy. There were no pickles or kimchi or any of the sides that usually come with jjigae. I guess they are in Williamsburg and catering to the crowd but there are so many decent Korean places in Brooklyn that are so much better than this place.
Got delivery from here and it was really good! Will come by once opened back up.

We went with my friends to this restaurant last night. The food was excellent, Korean dishes prepared to perfection. Cocktails were also very good. The staff, however, is certainly the best thing about the restaurant, they were very kind and very accommodating. I recommend this place and will definitely be back!

Finally some good Korean spicy pork bbq in Williamsburg! More vegetable variety and smokiness elevates the dish without losing the authentic flavor. Spiciness is a bit mild so if you like yours spicy ask for it or get gochujang on the side.
Great place to hang out with ur friends

Came here to grab some drinks on a friday night. This was a very good choice!! 👍😁 it was not crowded and the atmosphere was very relaxing and chill. They had a good variety of drinks, whether it was mixed drinks, beer or others (like soju). I got their jalapeno margarita 0w0, which was very good with a nice heat to it. And the food!!! I really like the korean fusion style of food. (Kind of sad that they didnt have tteokbooki on their menu but..  it's ok) For our first round, we ordered their fried chicken (half soy garlic and half sweet and spicy level 2) kimchi cheese fries and one of their spicy beef rice bowls. All were veryyyy good!! 🤗 the fries were nice and crispy and really went well with the kimchi and cheese. Their chicken wings were good too but the spicy one... wasn't really what I expected... not spicy enough either. Because of this we got the second round of boneless fried chicken with their korean bbq flavor. This one was pretty good, compared to the sweet and spicy one. We also got another fries: the garlic butter parmesan cheese. This one was slightly sweeter than I expected... when eaten with the korean bbq chicken.. (which was on the saltier side...) but all was still good 0w0. I'm glad I found this place. We will definitely be visiting again in the future 😁

First off, THANK YOU HARMONY!!! Harmony helped me out so much while I was here. I was throwing a birthday party for my wife and I wasn't aware of the updated food menu and was completely thrown off because there were some diet restrictions one of my wife's friend has. Harmony talked to the chef for me and the chef came out to discuss the menu with me and was able to make things from the old menu that they had for our group of 11-12 which was amazing. The food was great, I felt extremely welcome by every worker there including the manager, the cocktails are fantastic, we ended the night with some karaoke that they set up for us in the back and we danced. Such a gem of a place and you will be treated with nothing but kindness. Thank you for everything guys! We all had a great night.

Food was fantastic! The textures of the food were great and the seasoning....OMG. The seasoning for all 3 tapas, one entree, one dessert and 2 cocktails were out of this world. As a Korean food connoisseur this was definitely one of the best flavored Korean foods I have ever had but the only place in which I tasted the passion and heart of the chef in the food. This place is one of a kind. And to think this wasn't in KTown or JTown or Flushing, this was in Williamsburg! I will definitely be trekking to the place again even though it is 75 minutes away from my home. Yessss!!!

I happened to find this place by accident wasn’t even really looking for food but saw spicy raw octopus on the menu. So I decided to go in side great vibe cool looking place. I ordered the spicy octopus and decided to try the fried squid legs. Got it to go.  The spicy octopus had great flavor I enjoyed it. But the fried squid legs were cold and had a old oil taste to it. It may have tasted better it they were hot. I called back to tell them about my experience with the food. And asked if I could bring the squid legs back and exchange for something else.  Needless to say at this point I didn’t like the service. It was only about $5 on happy hour menu.  I was willing to walk back and exchange. This really killed the things that I liked about the restaurant.  Very disappointed because it was a cool Korean restaurant that I wanted to bring friends for a good experience.  That won’t be happening!
